  <div class="panel-body">
The children : The Lost Boys of Sudan were a group of orphaned children who walked a thousand miles to freedom during the Sudanese civil war. They were forced to leave their families and homes because violence, turmoil, and political instability in the area threatened their safety. The violence continues to this day. Some of the Lost Boys made it out alive and have moved to the US as well as other countries, who have provided financial and military support to the rebel forces in the area.
