<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">The Book: What is the What</div>
  <div class="panel-body">
What is the What is a book written by Dave Eggers (put picture of him on the side or something) in 2006 as an autobiography of Valentino Achak Deng, a lost boy, who with others like him was separated from his family during the Sudanese Civil War. Though the book is listed as a fiction novel, it contains accounts of real events as told to Eggers by Valentino. While most of the story is accurate in terms of its validity, some of the aspects in the writing were exaggerated with a “creative license” to make it more appealing to readers. Nevertheless the book went on to receive generally positive reviews from critics and it easily became a New York Times bestseller.
  </div>
</div>


